136
00:08:55,530 --> 00:08:56,960
After we graduate,

137
00:08:57,050 --> 00:08:59,050
you want to open a restaurant, right?

138
00:09:02,410 --> 00:09:04,470
Then we'll have to use a lot of money.

139
00:09:05,570 --> 00:09:08,700
I might have to borrow my dad's money
to open the restaurant.

140
00:09:10,130 --> 00:09:11,050
Wait a second.

141
00:09:11,190 --> 00:09:12,050
Dean.

142
00:09:12,650 --> 00:09:15,810
It's my restaurant. Why do we have to
borrow your dad's money?

143
00:09:17,510 --> 00:09:20,110
We are living together.
We have to help each other.

144
00:09:21,110 --> 00:09:21,950
But...

145
00:09:22,150 --> 00:09:24,150
You don't want to live with me?

146
00:09:25,210 --> 00:09:27,090
It's not that.

147
00:09:28,870 --> 00:09:30,270
I love you.

148
00:09:37,570 --> 00:09:39,210
I love you too.

149
00:09:40,530 --> 00:09:42,190
I want to be with you.

150
00:09:45,290 --> 00:09:47,230
I want to be with you, too.

151
00:09:49,450 --> 00:09:51,250
After we graduate,

152
00:09:51,790 --> 00:09:53,690
let's move in together.

153
00:10:07,810 --> 00:10:09,270
Why are you crying?

154
00:10:10,330 --> 00:10:11,550
Don't cry.

155
00:10:17,650 --> 00:10:18,490
You...

156
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:22,970
You said it like you're
asking me to marry you.

157
00:10:37,150 --> 00:10:38,600
I am asking you now.

158
00:10:41,990 --> 00:10:43,050
Dean...

159
00:10:46,590 --> 00:10:48,610
Your mum lives in New York, right?

160
00:10:49,570 --> 00:10:51,210
If I remember correctly,

161
00:10:51,390 --> 00:10:55,210
same-sex marriage is legal there.

162
00:11:05,030 --> 00:11:06,250
Come on.

163
00:11:06,930 --> 00:11:08,700
Let's dig in.

164
00:11:08,790 --> 00:11:10,390
You have to eat a lot.

165
00:11:12,630 --> 00:11:14,340
Don't change the topic yet.

166
00:11:14,430 --> 00:11:16,430
This is a big deal.

167
00:11:19,910 --> 00:11:21,540
Yes, it's a big deal.

168
00:11:22,570 --> 00:11:23,890
But in the end,

169
00:11:24,430 --> 00:11:26,530
it's still our decision, isn't it?

170
00:11:29,570 --> 00:11:31,030
That's true.

171
00:11:35,470 --> 00:11:37,610
Stop overthinking.

172
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,550
We still have a lot of time to think

173
00:11:41,630 --> 00:11:43,630
until we graduate.

174
00:11:44,710 --> 00:11:46,590
If nothing changes,

175
00:11:48,650 --> 00:11:50,650
I will ask you again.

176
00:11:51,250 --> 00:11:52,350
Okay?

177
00:11:53,110 --> 00:11:54,270
Okay.

178
00:12:01,790 --> 00:12:03,510
Let's dig in.

179
00:12:03,630 --> 00:12:05,470
It won't taste good if it gets cold.

180
00:12:09,930 --> 00:12:10,870
Look at this.

181
00:12:11,310 --> 00:12:13,090
It looks yummy.

182
00:12:14,550 --> 00:12:16,560
You have to finish the whole thing, then.

183
00:12:17,730 --> 00:12:18,990
Of course,

184
00:12:19,110 --> 00:12:20,990
I will finish the whole thing.

185
00:13:01,900 --> 00:13:03,400
Oh shoot!

186
00:13:17,780 --> 00:13:19,150
What are you doing?

187
00:13:21,580 --> 00:13:22,720
Nothing.

188
00:13:40,460 --> 00:13:41,780
You found it?

189
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:46,460
When did you buy it?

190
00:13:48,650 --> 00:13:50,840
When you went to throw away
your bubble tea.

191
00:13:53,580 --> 00:13:55,280
Why did you buy it?

192
00:13:57,740 --> 00:14:00,240
Didn't you learn about this
in health education?

193
00:14:00,420 --> 00:14:03,000
This is very important.

194
00:14:04,020 --> 00:14:05,820
It's about hygiene

195
00:14:05,900 --> 00:14:07,670
and safety.

196
00:14:25,310 --> 00:14:26,600
Dean.

197
00:14:34,940 --> 00:14:36,540
