260
00:21:31,820 --> 00:21:33,320
Let me see.

261
00:21:58,000 --> 00:21:59,920
[Be gentle with him, dude!]

262
00:22:09,020 --> 00:22:11,180
I don't think you need to take
fever medicine.

263
00:22:12,280 --> 00:22:14,040
And for other parts...

264
00:22:16,580 --> 00:22:18,280
Is there any part that still hurts?

265
00:22:21,800 --> 00:22:23,720
Did you buy all this?

266
00:22:25,120 --> 00:22:26,420
Pharm.

267
00:22:27,080 --> 00:22:28,920
Are you really okay?

268
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:36,440
Are you alright?

269
00:22:37,020 --> 00:22:38,480
I'm fine.

270
00:24:02,080 --> 00:24:05,340
Come on, let's play!

271
00:24:05,460 --> 00:24:06,300
In.

272
00:24:28,460 --> 00:24:29,880
In,

273
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:32,920
I love you.

274
00:24:50,150 --> 00:24:51,020
Dean.

275
00:24:56,460 --> 00:24:57,500
Dean.

276
00:25:06,380 --> 00:25:07,340
Dean.

277
00:25:09,840 --> 00:25:10,780
Dean.

278
00:25:13,140 --> 00:25:14,260
Dean.

279
00:25:16,900 --> 00:25:17,740
Pharm.

280
00:25:39,740 --> 00:25:41,560
Pharm, don't leave me.

281
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:47,120
Where can I go?

282
00:25:48,020 --> 00:25:49,640
I belong to you.

283
00:25:54,620 --> 00:25:56,820
No matter what happens,

284
00:25:58,340 --> 00:25:59,800
I'm right here.

285
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:02,320
Think of me.

286
00:26:02,640 --> 00:26:04,280
Do you understand?

287
00:26:08,890 --> 00:26:11,080
You'll be the first person
that I think of.

288
00:27:14,010 --> 00:27:15,620
Since when?

289
00:27:18,440 --> 00:27:20,440
When did you have someone spy on me?

290
00:27:20,520 --> 00:27:21,980
You answer me!

291
00:27:22,070 --> 00:27:23,840
Since when did you go out with this boy?

292
00:27:23,930 --> 00:27:26,160
This is my personal life!

293
00:27:26,250 --> 00:27:27,410
You two have to break up.

294
00:27:27,500 --> 00:27:30,780
It doesn't matter which girl
you go out with.

295
00:27:30,870 --> 00:27:32,640
But you cannot go out with a boy.

296
00:27:33,240 --> 00:27:34,300
Dad!

297
00:27:35,220 --> 00:27:39,180
Other people will say
that my son is abnormal.

298
00:27:42,490 --> 00:27:45,040
It doesn't matter what other people say.

299
00:27:45,130 --> 00:27:46,660
We didn't do anything wrong.

300
00:27:46,740 --> 00:27:49,140
I won't let you. I cannot accept this!

301
00:27:49,820 --> 00:27:52,150
Don't you dare go to see him again.

302
00:27:55,870 --> 00:27:57,530
You cannot force me.

303
00:28:00,070 --> 00:28:02,120
What are you going to do?

304
00:28:03,100 --> 00:28:05,860
Just go back to your room.
If you dare to go against me...

305
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,590
This boy will be in trouble.

306
00:28:50,810 --> 00:28:51,960
Bro.

307
00:28:53,370 --> 00:28:55,110
What's the matter?

308
00:29:16,630 --> 00:29:18,520
I heard you and Dad talking.

309
00:29:26,790 --> 00:29:27,960
I also know that

310
00:29:28,660 --> 00:29:30,120
you have a boyfriend.

311
00:29:31,600 --> 00:29:32,860
How did you know?

312
00:29:35,910 --> 00:29:37,030
A few days ago,

313
00:29:38,280 --> 00:29:41,370
I saw you walking with Intouch.

314
00:29:42,700 --> 00:29:44,200
We're just friends.

315
00:29:45,300 --> 00:29:47,250
You won't smile at a friend that way.

316
00:29:47,620 --> 00:29:48,900
I know.

317
00:29:48,980 --> 00:29:52,810
I can see the difference in your smile.

318
00:29:58,460 --> 00:29:59,930
Also,

319
00:30:00,920 --> 00:30:04,340
you look much happier
when you're with him.

320
00:30:05,900 --> 00:30:06,740
Korn.

321
00:30:09,670 --> 00:30:11,650
Whatever you do that makes you happy,

322
00:30:12,260 --> 00:30:13,500
just do it.

323
00:30:14,280 --> 00:30:16,010
About Dad's work,

324
00:30:17,380 --> 00:30:18,890
I can deal with that.

325
00:30:20,090 --> 00:30:21,060
Krit.

326
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:23,430
Don't say that.

327
00:30:24,940 --> 00:30:26,970
You said you wanted to be a policeman.

328
00:30:31,930 --> 00:30:33,270
That will be hard.

329
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:37,270
Our dad hates policemen.

330
00:30:37,700 --> 00:30:38,580
Krit.

331
00:30:39,100 --> 00:30:40,550
But dad's work

332
00:30:40,910 --> 00:30:42,950
is illegal.

333
00:30:43,490 --> 00:30:45,340
I don't want you to get involved.

334
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:47,190
Do you understand?

335
00:30:48,760 --> 00:30:49,560
But...

336
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:51,270
There are no buts, Krit.

337
00:30:54,460 --> 00:30:56,130
Just be whatever you want to be.

338
00:30:56,500 --> 00:30:57,990
Do you understand?

339
00:31:00,420 --> 00:31:01,460
Got it.

340
00:31:03,900 --> 00:31:05,450
You too.

341
00:31:05,640 --> 00:31:07,050
Don't just think about us.

342
00:31:07,130 --> 00:31:09,130
Think about your own happiness as well.

343
00:31:12,610 --> 00:31:13,960
You have to be a policeman.

344
00:31:14,460 --> 00:31:16,180
Take good care of Kard.

345
00:31:16,810 --> 00:31:18,040
Do you understand?

346
00:31:18,680 --> 00:31:20,070
I understand.

347
00:31:20,540 --> 00:31:21,840
I'm so great.

348
00:31:21,930 --> 00:31:23,060
I can do it.

349
00:31:25,530 --> 00:31:26,570
That's right.

350
00:31:33,580 --> 00:31:34,420
Go.

351
00:31:35,350 --> 00:31:36,410
Go back to your room

352
00:31:37,080 --> 00:31:38,620
before dad sees you here.

353
00:31:39,190 --> 00:31:40,650
You will get into trouble.

354
00:31:54,300 --> 00:31:55,860
Let's talk tomorrow, then.

355
00:32:29,600 --> 00:32:30,930
Your hands are very cold.

356
00:32:32,000 --> 00:32:33,950
I've never met him before.

357
00:32:34,260 --> 00:32:37,520
I've never met my uncle or my grandpa.

358
00:32:38,240 --> 00:32:41,360
My mum told me I met him
when I was really young.

359
00:32:41,440 --> 00:32:43,190
But I couldn't remember anything.

360
00:32:44,780 --> 00:32:48,210
You guys are related.
I don't think it's going to be a problem.

361
00:32:51,010 --> 00:32:52,190
I'm scared somehow.

362
00:32:55,470 --> 00:32:57,930
You've set my number
as an emergency number, right?

363
00:32:58,240 --> 00:32:59,250
If anything goes wrong,

364
00:32:59,340 --> 00:33:00,500
or if you want me to pick you up,

365
00:33:00,580 --> 00:33:01,790
call me right away.

366
00:33:02,990 --> 00:33:03,830
Okay.

367
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:16,460
Next school break,

368
00:33:16,800 --> 00:33:18,320
let's go to the States.

369
00:33:18,930 --> 00:33:20,530
I told your mum already.

370
00:33:22,770 --> 00:33:24,100
Are you serious?

371
00:33:25,260 --> 00:33:26,460
I'm serious.

372
00:33:27,120 --> 00:33:28,930
I've already told my parents, too.

373
00:33:29,260 --> 00:33:30,570
Maybe

374
00:33:30,660 --> 00:33:32,350
my parents will come with us.

375
00:33:33,620 --> 00:33:36,340
Grandma might come too.

376
00:33:38,980 --> 00:33:40,300
An is coming too?

377
00:33:40,720 --> 00:33:42,000
Alin...

378
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:43,790
I mean, your mum too?

379
00:33:45,600 --> 00:33:46,850
Of course.

380
00:33:47,310 --> 00:33:51,160
My family said since I took you in,

381
00:33:51,570 --> 00:33:53,810
I have to show my responsibility.

382
00:34:00,050 --> 00:34:02,630
My cousin is already 15 minutes late.

383
00:34:03,900 --> 00:34:06,590
My mum didn't give me
his phone number either.

384
00:34:10,210 --> 00:34:14,370
If he doesn't show up within the hour,
I will take you back.

385
00:34:15,330 --> 00:34:16,750
That won't be necessary.

386
00:34:17,449 --> 00:34:18,679
I've been here for a while already.

387
00:34:18,770 --> 00:34:19,909
I saw you two talking.

388
00:34:20,000 --> 00:34:21,730
I didn't want to interrupt.

389
00:34:27,699 --> 00:34:29,489
Hello, Cousin.

390
00:34:29,570 --> 00:34:30,770
Are you ready?

391
00:34:32,739 --> 00:34:33,760
Silp.

392
00:34:36,060 --> 00:34:37,790
You're his cousin?

393
00:34:38,940 --> 00:34:39,790
Yes.

394
00:34:49,420 --> 00:34:50,420
Pharm.

395
00:34:50,690 --> 00:34:51,940
Don't forget.

396
00:34:52,100 --> 00:34:54,429
If anything happens, just call me anytime.

397
00:34:56,110 --> 00:34:56,949
Okay.

398
00:34:57,660 --> 00:34:59,170
I will leave then.

399
00:35:00,960 --> 00:35:03,310
Please look after him for me.

400
00:35:29,310 --> 00:35:30,690
Are you surprised?

401
00:35:32,900 --> 00:35:33,740
Yes.

402
00:35:34,020 --> 00:35:36,290
I've only just found out
you're my cousin as well.

403
00:35:38,450 --> 00:35:40,050
Since when did you know?

404
00:35:40,580 --> 00:35:41,420
Since...

405
00:35:41,840 --> 00:35:43,730
Since I knew which room was yours.

406
00:35:47,940 --> 00:35:49,040
That's a while ago.

407
00:35:49,120 --> 00:35:51,230
Why didn't you tell me?

408
00:35:52,540 --> 00:35:54,770
My dad bought two rooms.

409
00:35:54,980 --> 00:35:57,160
The big one is for me
and my younger brother.

410
00:35:57,250 --> 00:35:59,420
The other one is for my little sister.

411
00:35:59,580 --> 00:36:02,370
But right now, my sister is living abroad.

412
00:36:02,560 --> 00:36:05,390
After I graduated, I bought
the room from my dad.

413
00:36:06,020 --> 00:36:08,640
My younger brother got into
the university in the city.

414
00:36:08,720 --> 00:36:10,560
He's actually looking for
a place to stay right now.

415
00:36:10,640 --> 00:36:13,410
My dad saw that the room was available,
so he let you stay instead.

416
00:36:16,420 --> 00:36:19,390
So, you are my mum's spy.

417
00:36:20,880 --> 00:36:23,330
In exchange, I got a collection
of shoes from the USA.

418
00:36:23,410 --> 00:36:26,110
I didn't let you know at first
because I felt sorry for you.

419
00:36:31,740 --> 00:36:34,050
If I had shown myself as your cousin,

420
00:36:34,130 --> 00:36:36,130
Dean wouldn't be able
to do anything to you.

421
00:36:43,360 --> 00:36:44,910
You know?

422
00:36:46,990 --> 00:36:50,220
The walls of this condo
might block some sound,

423
00:36:50,300 --> 00:36:52,750
but the door on the balcony doesn't.

424
00:36:52,830 --> 00:36:53,670
As it happens,

425
00:36:53,760 --> 00:36:55,760
I like to smoke on the balcony.

426
00:36:58,800 --> 00:37:01,970
Dean didn't tell you I gave you
all those medicines?

427
00:37:02,950 --> 00:37:03,940
He didn't.

428
00:37:09,230 --> 00:37:11,230
Dean is nice to you, right?

429
00:37:13,730 --> 00:37:15,420
He is very kind.

430
00:37:18,740 --> 00:37:19,940
That night,

431
00:37:20,030 --> 00:37:22,610
I had already planned that if you
kept crying and Dean wouldn't stop,

432
00:37:22,690 --> 00:37:24,700
I would climb over to your room.

433
00:37:28,480 --> 00:37:29,380
Silp...

434
00:37:34,480 --> 00:37:36,270
What is your dad like?

435
00:37:41,250 --> 00:37:42,580
My dad?

436
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:45,170
He used to be a policeman.

437
00:37:45,260 --> 00:37:46,740
He was a workaholic.

438
00:37:46,820 --> 00:37:48,060
But he's retired now.

439
00:37:48,660 --> 00:37:49,970
He's very straightforward.

440
00:37:50,060 --> 00:37:51,360
He's very strict.

441
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:52,980
He wouldn't give me any information
when I asked.

442
00:37:53,060 --> 00:37:53,840
Also,

443
00:37:53,920 --> 00:37:55,660
he's an old man who tends to sulk a lot.

444
00:38:09,710 --> 00:38:11,100
Actually, he's a very kind uncle.

445
00:38:11,180 --> 00:38:11,970
He loves his family.

446
00:38:12,050 --> 00:38:13,540
He's a reasonable man.

447
00:38:22,990 --> 00:38:23,980
Are you ready?

448
00:38:26,500 --> 00:38:27,090
Yes.

449
00:38:27,170 --> 00:38:28,210
Let's go.

450
00:38:39,340 --> 00:38:41,710
Silp and Pharm are cousins?

451
00:38:43,170 --> 00:38:44,860
He never told you that?

452
00:38:47,360 --> 00:38:49,420
We don't really talk about his family.

453
00:38:52,350 --> 00:38:55,520
I understand now why he cares
about Pharm so much.

454
00:39:13,440 --> 00:39:14,640
Sorn.

455
00:39:16,480 --> 00:39:18,380
What is Silp's surname?

456
00:39:27,700 --> 00:39:29,340
You really don't know?

457
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:32,130
His dad appears on TV quite often.

458
00:39:35,810 --> 00:39:37,360
I really don't know.

459
00:39:45,540 --> 00:39:46,860
Ariyasakul.

460
00:39:53,170 --> 00:39:55,980
Silp's surname is Ariyasakul.

461
00:40:06,220 --> 00:40:07,090
Korn.

462
00:40:07,260 --> 00:40:09,090
Wait for me.

463
00:40:12,290 --> 00:40:13,780
I told you to stop bothering me.

464
00:40:13,860 --> 00:40:15,760
Don't you know my name?

465
00:40:16,030 --> 00:40:17,250
I know.

466
00:40:17,330 --> 00:40:19,790
How can I not know the name
of someone I like?

467
00:40:20,240 --> 00:40:22,800
Korn Ariyasakul. That's your name.

468
00:40:41,100 --> 00:40:41,940
Dean.

469
00:40:44,450 --> 00:40:45,290
Dean.

470
00:40:45,680 --> 00:40:46,620
Dean.

471
00:40:47,890 --> 00:40:48,950
Dean.

472
00:40:49,870 --> 00:40:51,100
What's wrong?

473
00:40:52,130 --> 00:40:53,130
Nothing.

474
00:41:01,230 --> 00:41:02,270
Pharm.

475
00:41:35,240 --> 00:41:36,500
[Next episode]

476
00:41:46,120 --> 00:41:46,960
Dad.

477
00:41:47,400 --> 00:41:48,920
What's your older brother's name?
